Note: ============================================================================
Note: Dart Parser - Complete AST generation for Dart 3.x
Note: Part of Translation Translation System
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/dart/dart_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListOps

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Type Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant DART_PROGRAM as Integer is 7000
Constant DART_IMPORT_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 7001
Constant DART_EXPORT_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 7002
Constant DART_LIBRARY_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 7003
Constant DART_PART_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 7004
Constant DART_CLASS_DECL as Integer is 7010
Constant DART_ENUM_DECL as Integer is 7011
Constant DART_TYPEDEF_DECL as Integer is 7012
Constant DART_EXTENSION_DECL as Integer is 7013
Constant DART_MIXIN_DECL as Integer is 7014
Constant DART_FUNCTION_DECL as Integer is 7020
Constant DART_METHOD_DECL as Integer is 7021
Constant DART_GETTER_DECL as Integer is 7022
Constant DART_SETTER_DECL as Integer is 7023
Constant DART_CONSTRUCTOR_DECL as Integer is 7024
Constant DART_FACTORY_DECL as Integer is 7025
Constant DART_FIELD_DECL as Integer is 7030
Constant DART_VARIABLE_DECL as Integer is 7031
Constant DART_PARAMETER as Integer is 7040
Constant DART_NAMED_PARAMETER as Integer is 7041
Constant DART_OPTIONAL_PARAMETER as Integer is 7042
Constant DART_TYPE_ANNOTATION as Integer is 7050
Constant DART_GENERIC_TYPE as Integer is 7051
Constant DART_FUNCTION_TYPE as Integer is 7052
Constant DART_NULLABLE_TYPE as Integer is 7053
Constant DART_BLOCK_STMT as Integer is 7060
Constant DART_RETURN_STMT as Integer is 7061
Constant DART_IF_STMT as Integer is 7062
Constant DART_FOR_STMT as Integer is 7063
Constant DART_WHILE_STMT as Integer is 7064
Constant DART_DO_WHILE_STMT as Integer is 7065
Constant DART_SWITCH_STMT as Integer is 7066
Constant DART_TRY_STMT as Integer is 7067
Constant DART_THROW_STMT as Integer is 7068
Constant DART_BREAK_STMT as Integer is 7069
Constant DART_CONTINUE_STMT as Integer is 7070
Constant DART_EXPR_STMT as Integer is 7080
Constant DART_BINARY_EXPR as Integer is 7081
Constant DART_UNARY_EXPR as Integer is 7082
Constant DART_CALL_EXPR as Integer is 7083
Constant DART_INDEX_EXPR as Integer is 7084
Constant DART_MEMBER_EXPR as Integer is 7085
Constant DART_CONDITIONAL_EXPR as Integer is 7086
Constant DART_CASCADE_EXPR as Integer is 7087
Constant DART_AWAIT_EXPR as Integer is 7088
Constant DART_LITERAL_EXPR as Integer is 7090
Constant DART_LIST_LITERAL as Integer is 7091
Constant DART_MAP_LITERAL as Integer is 7092
Constant DART_SET_LITERAL as Integer is 7093
Constant DART_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 7094
Constant DART_THIS_EXPR as Integer is 7095
Constant DART_SUPER_EXPR as Integer is 7096
Constant DART_NULL_EXPR as Integer is 7097
Constant DART_ASSIGNMENT_EXPR as Integer is 7098
Constant DART_LAMBDA_EXPR as Integer is 7099

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
DartParser holds the lexer pointer, current token cache, full token list (collected up front for backtrack-free parsing), cursor position, and error list. Caching the entire token list lets the parser do arbitrary lookahead without re-lexing.
@End Reasoning
Type called "DartParser":
    lexer as Integer
    current_token as Integer
    tokens as Integer
    position as Integer
    errors as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Construction allocates the parser, pre-tokenizes the entire source into a token list, and initializes position to 0. Front-loading lexing means parse-time lookups are O(1) list-indexing rather than re-running the lexer's state machine.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_dart_parser" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create parser from lexer

    Let parser be proc arena_alloc from Arena with 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 0, lexer

    Let tokens be proc create_list from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 16, tokens

    Note: Collect all tokens
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token be proc next_token from Lexer with lexer
        proc list_append from ListOps with tokens, token

        Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 0
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            If 1 is equal to 1:
                Note: Break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:
                    Note: Force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 24, 0

    Note: Set first token as current
    Let first_token be proc list_get from ListOps with tokens, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 8, first_token

    Let errors be proc create_list from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 32, errors

    Return parser
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Utility Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Returns the token type tag at the cursor without consuming; productions use this for one-token lookahead during recursive-descent dispatch.
@End Reasoning
Process called "current_token_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token type

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 0
    Return token_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bumps the cursor and refreshes the cached current_token. The cache is updated here (not on every peek) because most productions peek multiple times before advancing.
@End Reasoning
Process called "advance_parser" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Advance to next token

    Let position be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 24
    Let tokens be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 16
    Let token_count be proc list_length from ListOps with tokens

    Set position to position plus 1

    If position is greater than or equal to token_count:
        Set position to token_count minus 1
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 24, position

    Let token be proc list_get from ListOps with tokens, position
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser, 8, token

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Canonical recursive-descent expect: matches the current token type or records an error and returns 0 without advancing. The non-advancing behavior on mismatch lets callers recover by trying a different production.
@End Reasoning
Process called "expect_token" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Expect and consume specific token type

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    If token_type is not equal to expected_type:
        proc add_parse_error with parser, "Unexpected token"
        Return 0
    End If

    proc advance_parser from parser
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Soft version of expect_token: returns 1 (and advances) if the current token matches, 0 otherwise (without error). Used for optional terminals in grammar productions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "match_token" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if current token matches type

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to expected_type:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends an error message (with current position) to the parser's error list; the list is collected over the parse and returned by the orchestrator for unified diagnostic display.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_parse_error" takes parser as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add parse error to error list

    Let errors be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 32
    proc list_append from ListOps with errors, message
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Creates an AST node with the given type tag and initializes empty children/value/metadata slots. The factory pattern centralizes node-shape conventions so productions don't repeat the allocation boilerplate.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_ast_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create AST node with type

    Let node be proc arena_alloc from Arena with 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, node_type

    Let children be proc create_list from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 24, children
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 32, 0

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a child to a node's children list; null children are skipped to keep the AST clean when optional sub-productions return nothing.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_node_child" takes node as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add child to AST node

    If child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 24
    proc list_append from ListOps with children, child

    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 32
    Set count to count plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 32, count

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sets the node's primary value (identifier string, literal value, etc.); the value's interpretation depends on the node type tag.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_node_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node value (string data)

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, value
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Attaches arbitrary key/value metadata to a node (used for modifiers like "abstract", "static", "final" that are properties of declarations but don't fit cleanly into child positions).
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_node_metadata" takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node metadata

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 16, value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The top-level Dart compilation unit is "directives* top_level_declaration*". We parse directives first (library, import, export, part) then top-level declarations (class, enum, function, variable) until EOF, accumulating into the root NODE_PROGRAM.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_program" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse Dart program (compilation unit)

    @Reasoning:
    Dart program consists of:
    - Optional library directive
    - Import/export directives
    - Part directives
    - Top-level declarations (classes, functions, variables, etc.)
    @End Reasoning

    Let program be proc create_ast_node from DART_PROGRAM

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Return program
        End If

        Note: Parse directives
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_LIBRARY:
            Let directive be proc parse_library_directive from parser
            proc add_node_child with program, directive

        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IMPORT:
                Set directive to proc parse_import_directive from parser
                proc add_node_child with program, directive

            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EXPORT:
                    Set directive to proc parse_export_directive from parser
                    proc add_node_child with program, directive

                Otherwise:
                    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_PART:
                        Set directive to proc parse_part_directive from parser
                        proc add_node_child with program, directive

                    Otherwise:
                        Note: Parse top-level declarations
                        Let decl be proc parse_top_level_declaration from parser
                        If decl is not equal to 0:
                            proc add_node_child with program, decl

                        Otherwise:
                            proc advance_parser from parser
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return program
End Process

@Reasoning:
"library name.path;" declares a library identifier; we capture the dotted name for use by import resolution. There must be at most one library directive per file (Dart spec requirement, validated downstream).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_library_directive" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse library directive

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_LIBRARY

    Let directive be proc create_ast_node from DART_LIBRARY_DIRECTIVE

    Note: Parse library name
    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with directive, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_DOT:
            proc advance_parser from parser
            Set token to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
            Set lexeme to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
            proc advance_parser from parser

        Otherwise:
            If 1 is equal to 1:
                Note: Break
                If 1 is not equal to 1:
                    Note: Force break
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON

    Return directive
End Process

@Reasoning:
"import 'uri' [as prefix] [show id, ...] [hide id, ...] [deferred]" with combinators in any order; we parse the URI first then iterate clauses. The combinators control symbol visibility from the imported library.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_import_directive" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse import directive

    @Reasoning:
    import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
    import 'dart:async' as async;
    import 'lib.dart' show foo, bar;
    import 'lib.dart' hide baz;
    import 'lib.dart' deferred as lib;
    @End Reasoning

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_IMPORT

    Let directive be proc create_ast_node from DART_IMPORT_DIRECTIVE

    Note: Parse URI string
    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with directive, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    Note: Parse optional clauses
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_DEFERRED:
            proc advance_parser from parser

        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_AS:
                proc advance_parser from parser
                Set token to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
                Set lexeme to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
                proc advance_parser from parser

            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_SHOW:
                    proc advance_parser from parser
                    Note: Parse show list
                    While 1 is equal to 1:
                        Set token to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
                        proc advance_parser from parser

                        Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
                        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                            proc advance_parser from parser

                        Otherwise:
                            If 1 is equal to 1:
                                Note: Break
                                If 1 is not equal to 1:
                                    Note: Force break
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End While

                Otherwise:
                    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_HIDE:
                        proc advance_parser from parser
                        Note: Parse hide list
                        While 1 is equal to 1:
                            Set token to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
                            proc advance_parser from parser

                            Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
                            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                                proc advance_parser from parser

                            Otherwise:
                                If 1 is equal to 1:
                                    Note: Break
                                    If 1 is not equal to 1:
                                        Note: Force break
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End While

                    Otherwise:
                        If 1 is equal to 1:
                            Note: Break
                            If 1 is not equal to 1:
                                Note: Force break
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON

    Return directive
End Process

@Reasoning:
"export 'uri' [show ...] [hide ...]" re-exports symbols from another library; shape parallels import but without prefix/deferred clauses (you can't rename what you export).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_export_directive" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse export directive

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_EXPORT

    Let directive be proc create_ast_node from DART_EXPORT_DIRECTIVE

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with directive, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON

    Return directive
End Process

@Reasoning:
"part 'file.dart';" (or "part of library_name;") splits a library across multiple files; the directive's URI/library reference is captured for the file-resolution system to assemble the full library.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_part_directive" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse part directive

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_PART

    Let directive be proc create_ast_node from DART_PART_DIRECTIVE

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with directive, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON

    Return directive
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Declaration Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Dispatch on the first token of a top-level form: "class" or "abstract class" -> class, "enum" -> enum, "typedef" -> typedef, "extension" -> extension, "mixin" -> mixin, otherwise parse_function_or_variable_declaration (which itself disambiguates between function and variable based on whether parens follow the identifier).
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_top_level_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse top-level declaration

    @Reasoning:
    Top-level declarations:
    - Class declarations
    - Enum declarations
    - Typedef declarations
    - Extension declarations
    - Mixin declarations
    - Function declarations
    - Variable declarations
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

    Note: Class declaration
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_ABSTRACT:
        proc advance_parser from parser
        Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_CLASS:
            Let decl be proc parse_class_declaration from parser
            Return decl
        End If
    End If

    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_CLASS:
        Set decl to proc parse_class_declaration from parser
        Return decl
    End If

    Note: Enum declaration
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_ENUM:
        Set decl to proc parse_enum_declaration from parser
        Return decl
    End If

    Note: Typedef declaration
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_TYPEDEF:
        Set decl to proc parse_typedef_declaration from parser
        Return decl
    End If

    Note: Extension declaration
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EXTENSION:
        Set decl to proc parse_extension_declaration from parser
        Return decl
    End If

    Note: Mixin declaration
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_MIXIN:
        Set decl to proc parse_mixin_declaration from parser
        Return decl
    End If

    Note: Function or variable declaration
    Set decl to proc parse_function_or_variable_declaration from parser
    Return decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
A Dart class is "[abstract] class Name [<TypeParams>] [extends Super] [with Mixin, ...] [implements Iface, ...] { members }". We collect modifiers, type parameters, superclass, mixins, and interfaces separately so semantic analysis can validate the conformance graph.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_class_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse class declaration

    @Reasoning:
    class MyClass extends BaseClass implements Interface1, Interface2 with Mixin1 {
      // members
    }
    @End Reasoning

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_CLASS

    Let class_decl be proc create_ast_node from DART_CLASS_DECL

    Note: Parse class name
    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with class_decl, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    Note: Parse optional type parameters
    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_LESS_THAN:
        proc parse_type_parameters from parser
    End If

    Note: Parse extends clause
    Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EXTENDS:
        proc advance_parser from parser
        Let base_type be proc parse_type_annotation from parser
        proc add_node_child with class_decl, base_type
    End If

    Note: Parse implements clause
    Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IMPLEMENTS:
        proc advance_parser from parser

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let interface_type be proc parse_type_annotation from parser
            proc add_node_child with class_decl, interface_type

            Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                proc advance_parser from parser

            Otherwise:
                If 1 is equal to 1:
                    Note: Break
                    If 1 is not equal to 1:
                        Note: Force break
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Note: Parse with clause (mixins)
    Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_WITH:
        proc advance_parser from parser

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let mixin_type be proc parse_type_annotation from parser
            proc add_node_child with class_decl, mixin_type

            Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
                proc advance_parser from parser

            Otherwise:
                If 1 is equal to 1:
                    Note: Break
                    If 1 is not equal to 1:
                        Note: Force break
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Note: Parse class body
    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_LEFT_BRACE

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_RIGHT_BRACE:
            proc advance_parser from parser
            Return class_decl
        End If

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Return class_decl
        End If

        Let member be proc parse_class_member from parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_node_child with class_decl, member

        Otherwise:
            proc advance_parser from parser
        End If
    End While

    Return class_decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dart enums are "enum Name { Val1, Val2, ... }" (simple) or "enum Name { Val1(args), ... ; members }" (enhanced with members and constructors). We parse the simple case and the enhanced case uniformly with optional members section.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_enum_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse enum declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_ENUM

    Let enum_decl be proc create_ast_node from DART_ENUM_DECL

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with enum_decl, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_LEFT_BRACE

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_RIGHT_BRACE:
            proc advance_parser from parser
            Return enum_decl
        End If

        Set token to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
        Set lexeme to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
        proc advance_parser from parser

        Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_COMMA:
            proc advance_parser from parser

        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_RIGHT_BRACE:
                proc advance_parser from parser
                Return enum_decl
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return enum_decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
"typedef Name = Type;" creates a type alias. Older Dart used "typedef ReturnType Name(params);" for function-type aliases; we accept both forms because they coexist in real-world Dart code.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_typedef_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse typedef declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_TYPEDEF

    Let typedef_decl be proc create_ast_node from DART_TYPEDEF_DECL

    Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
    Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
    proc set_node_value with typedef_decl, lexeme
    proc advance_parser from parser

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_SEMICOLON

    Return typedef_decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
"extension [Name] [<TypeParams>] on Type { members }" adds members to an existing type without modifying its source. The optional name lets the extension be referred to explicitly when multiple extensions would otherwise conflict.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_extension_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse extension declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_EXTENSION

    Let extension_decl be proc create_ast_node from DART_EXTENSION_DECL

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_IDENTIFIER:
        Let token be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser, 8
        Let lexeme be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token, 8
        proc set_node_value with extension_decl, lexeme
        proc advance_parser from parser
    End If

    Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser
    If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_ON:
        proc advance_parser from parser
        Let target_type be proc parse_type_annotation from parser
        proc add_node_child with extension_decl, target_type
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_LEFT_BRACE

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Set token_type to proc current_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to Lexer.TOKEN_RIGHT_BRACE:
            proc advance_parser from parser
            Return extension_decl
        End If

        Let member be proc parse_class_member from parser
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc add_node_child with extension_decl, member

        Otherwise:
            proc advance_parser from parser
        End If
    End While

    Return extension_decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
"mixin Name [on Constraint] [implements Iface, ...] { members }" declares a reusable behavior bundle; the "on" clause constrains which classes can use this mixin. We capture all three (name, constraints, interfaces) separately.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_mixin_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse mixin declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, Lexer.TOKEN_MIXIN

